 <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=92172 "><IMG SRC="http://www.angelfire.com/rpg2/fierios/Toxx.txt" HEIGHT=168 WIDTH=375></a></center><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukerryndarkwater.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kerryn Darkwater</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1473<br> <font color=#E9D756>(5/4/02 6:42:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3320.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Wrong way round</span><hr size=1> I've beta tested a few games now over the past few years. I'm currently on 3 games, 2 of which I actually play on a regular basis.<br>
<br>
One is a pc game.<br>
<br>
The second is Earth and Beyond. A mmorpg game set in space. ( They don't mind me telling you that )<br>
<br>
The third is a PS2 game that I wish I'd never got involved with because it's too damn buggy. This one is from a British company but it shouldn't be in beta. It's nowhere near ready for that stage.<br>
<br>
The one thing I have to say is that all of them go out of their way to make my time worthwhile. From one I get a shedload of vouchers which really helps with my gaming addictions. One sends me merchandise, game controllers, some funky stuff.<br>
<br>
Westwood haven't given me anything but last time I beta tested one of their games ( Nox ) they gave me a 700mhz processor for my computer when I was done.<br>
<br>
All of them Ive tested send the discs direct to my door in a nicely packaged box. It says Dear Sir on the top of the letter and the GMs or developers treat me with the utmost respect.<br>
<br>
In return I'm expected to play these games till my fingers bleed. Im expected to download potentially harmful software, some of which can totally fry my hard drive. And I have to make notes of everything.<br>
<br>
If I play for 2 hours I have to log my time, tell them what I did during my time, did I die. What killed me? Were there any bugs? What sort of bug, what caused it, how did it affect gameplay, can I make it happen again, does it really need to be fixed, Did I enjoy my time? What made me switch off? When do I expect to play again? When did I actually play again? Do I sometimes get bored blah blah blah. The list goes on.<br>
<br>
But I do see a lot of people who fill in reports on the forum that say &quot;The spaceship should be red&quot;, &quot;I think there should be a lake there&quot;, &quot;Can we get some cool weapons?&quot;, &quot;I've been playing for a week now and I've crashed 6 times, this is @#%$ I'm not playing anymore&quot;<br>
<br>
I'm doing these companies a fvcking favour. Not the other way round. If some of you wouldn't bend over so often and let them shag you up the ass you'd all be beta testing the games you want, and you'd be compensted for it. Instead people as Bodie said think it's great to play a game which you'll probably be bored of by the time it's ready.<br>
<br>
But instead you talk about how they run a business and are there to make money, they are there to push you into paying for legends. I'm clear of EQ2. I will not play it.<br>
